                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i2">
                     <note>- On fol. 181ra, the Homily by Cyriacus of Behnesa [Laḥa Maryam “Lamentation of Mary”] (in Text I-10) ends with a note on the translation of the homily by ʾabba Sälama:</note>
                     <note>ዛቲ፡ መጽሐፍ፡ ዘተርጐማ፡ ብፁዕ፡ ወርቱዐ፡ ሃይማኖት፡ አቡነ፡ አባ፡ ሰላማ፡ ይጽሐፍ፡ ስሞ፡ ውስተ፡ መጽሐፈ፡ ሕይወት፡ በመንግሥተ፡ ሰማያት፡ ምስለ፡ ጸሐፊሃ፡ ወአጽሐፊሃ፡ ለዓለመ፡ ዓለም፡ አሜን።</note>
                     <note>The note it is separated from the main text with a chain of red and black dots.</note>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem xml:id="coloph1">
